<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
      Privacy manifest — macOS app (StandupTimer).
      Reflects the app's REAL behavior (issue #27):
        - No tracking, no analytics/ads SDK, no data sent to the developer.
          Meeting settings / stats / badges are stored locally (UserDefaults +
          on-disk JSON in the app container) and never leave the device.
        - Local-network usage was removed (issue #1); the GIF-search SDK was
          removed (issue #2) — neither is declared here.
        - Only required-reason API declared: UserDefaults (CA92.1), used for
          settings/stats/Pro-state persistence. No File-timestamp, disk-space,
          system-boot-time or active-keyboard APIs are used by the app code, so
          none are declared (do not over-declare).
        - ProAccessManager uses StoreKit (Apple's own purchase API) — Apple's
          purchase flow needs no extra app-manifest entry.

      FUTURE NOTE: when RevenueCat ships, the RevenueCat SDK bundles its OWN
      PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy inside the package, so its required-reason APIs and
      collected purchase data are declared there, not here. When iCloud sync
      ships, the synced data lives in the user's own iCloud account (not sent to
      the developer), so it is not "data collection" in the manifest sense.
      Revisit this file when either feature is wired into a shipping build.
    -->
    <!-- Analytics produit via PostHog (host EU) : interactions produit, sans
         tracking cross-app (NSPrivacyTracking = false, pas d'ATT). Le SDK PostHog
         embarque son propre manifeste pour ses required-reason APIs. -->
    <key>NSPrivacyTracking</key>
    <false/>
    <key>NSPrivacyTrackingDomains</key>
    <array/>
    <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes</key>
    <array>
        <dict>
            <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataType</key>
            <string>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypeProductInteraction</string>
            <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypeLinked</key>
            <false/>
            <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypeTracking</key>
            <false/>
            <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypePurposes</key>
            <array>
                <string>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypePurposeAnalytics</string>
            </array>
        </dict>
    </array>
    <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes</key>
    <array>
        <dict>
            <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPIType</key>
            <string>NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryUserDefaults</string>
            <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypeReasons</key>
            <array>
                <string>CA92.1</string>
            </array>
        </dict>
    </array>
</dict>
</plist>
